items.title: 2 Top Dividend Stocks to Buy If You Have $1,000 to Invest
items.author: Rachel Warren
items.description: The article discusses two dividend stocks, UnitedHealth Group and Costco Wholesale, that have the potential to deliver strong performance in the long term. UnitedHealth Group is a healthcare company with consistent dividend growth, while Costco Wholesale has a low dividend yield but a history of share price appreciation and special dividends.

insights.sentiment_reasoning: The article highlights UnitedHealth Group's consistent dividend growth, strong financial performance, and diversified business model, making it a potentially attractive long-term investment.
The article praises Costco Wholesale's business model, consistent dividend increases, and strong share price performance, suggesting it could be a good long-term dividend stock investment.
